        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/yoasif/{size}/3727_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-06-19T07:38:00.791Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I recently had a family member change to a new phone number.</p>\n<p>They signed up to Signal again with a new number and de-registered their old number as well.</p>\n<p>However, now my old messages with them appear under their old number and I have two ‚Äúconversations‚Äù open with them.</p>\n<p>I don‚Äôt want to archive my old conversation with them because it is still the same person, but there is no way to merge or migrate a dead conversation into a live one.</p>\n<p>I know of no way to manipulate my backups to accomplish this either, so a feature to migrate the old conversations into the number would be really handy.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 12,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-16T06:04:21.204Z",
