        "id": 35036,
        "name": null,
        "username": "IntentionalTypo",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/intentionaltypo/{size}/2100_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-06-19T11:39:53.335Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This could be abused in a nasty way. You could actually then attribute Alice‚Äôs chat history (merge) to a completely random Bob‚Äôs phone number (conversation) in Signal which could make it look like Bob‚Äôs phone number is talking to you when in actuality it was Alice‚Ä¶basically redirecting messages from appearing under its proper phone number to this (by your own choice) selected contact in your phonebook.</p>\n<p>For example,</p>\n<ul>\n<li>you get a separate phone number</li>\n<li>write some abusive and threatening messages</li>\n<li>merge with the person you don‚Äôt like</li>\n<li>go to the police with that</li>\n<li>open an investigation of that person you don‚Äôt like under false pretenses</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I don‚Äôt know‚Ä¶I have my doubts about this ‚Äúmerger feature‚Äù. It can be abused to spread FakeNews about particular people. If it can be done in a way that it is possible to have some sort of authentication that would prevent such a procedural exploit, it would be very welcome.</p>",
        "post_number": 3,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 12,
        "updated_at": "2019-06-19T11:40:59.442Z",
        "reply_count": 2,
