      {
        "id": 35039,
        "name": "Johanw666",
        "username": "johanw666",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/johanw666/{size}/9312_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-06-19T12:49:10.455Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"IntentionalTypo\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"8139\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/intentionaltypo/48/2100_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> IntentionalTypo:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I have my doubts about this ‚Äúmerger feature‚Äù. It can be abused to spread FakeNews about particular people</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>If it is usefull and important for people with enough resources any reasonably competent developer can build something that does this. If someone, say a state actor, thinks it can be used to implicate Trump, Putin, Iran or whoever, the NSA, FBI, FSB, Mossad or Cellebrite have more than enough knowledge to create something like that.</p>\n<p>Signal does not implement tamper protection, certainly not against someone having full local access. To defend against that you‚Äôd need some kind of blockchain technology, but that is very bad for other things like plausible deniability and anonimity.</p>",
