        "name": "[Android and Windows Beta]",
        "username": "TheCircle",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/f475e1/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2022-06-15T18:18:40.861Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi there, before signal added the ability to change phone number, one of my relatives had got a new phone number due moving countries and reinstalled signal as per the original instructions before phone number changing was possible.</p>\n<p>However, this means that I have old conversations which now says unsecured sms and then the new phone phone number conversation saying signal message.</p>\n<p>Is there a way to merge both conversations, so that messages on the previous conversation can be merged according to time and date sent?</p>\n<p>Maybe the ability to tap and hold on multiple conversations and then tap a merge button to merge the chats together.</p>",
