        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/reg67/{size}/54198_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-12-06T11:21:22.356Z",
        "cooked": "<p>That‚Äôs what happens with iMessage. E.g., if you add +1 800 100 2000 and <a href=\"mailto:bob1@icloud.com\">bob1@icloud.com</a> to the same contact, messages from +1 800 100 2000 and <a href=\"mailto:bob1@icloud.com\">bob1@icloud.com</a> will all be in the same thread, but can be separated (unmerged) if the contact is removed.</p>\n<p>I still haven‚Äôt tested out the edge cases for that yet. (e.g., when adding two identifiers to a single contact, which identifier will be texted to?)</p>\n<p>Signal should definitely be able to do this too. Signal can avoid edge cases, like adding two different persons contact identifiers into a single contact, by only allowing merging for deleted users.</p>",
